    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11 DU/2–653</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d276fn1">This message was transmitted to the Department of
                        State in telegram 1043, Feb. 6. with instructions that the Acting Secretary
                        forward it to the President. A handwritten notation in the margin of the
                        source text reads as follows: “Copy sent W[hite] h[ouse] Feb 6,
                        1953.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-06">February 6,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>:] Our trip to Bonn was, I believe,
                    constructive and useful. <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName>
                    believes he will be able to push ahead with <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>
                    despite tactics of opposition and difficult legal question involving <pb
                        facs="0504" n="1572" xml:id="pg_1572"/> German court. There is no flagging
                    in his determination to move ahead as rapidly as he possibly can.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d276fn2">For a record of <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName>’ and <persName corresp="#p_STASSENHE1"
                            >Stassen</persName>’s meeting with <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                            >Adenauer</persName> on Feb. 5, see telegram 1045 from The Hague, Feb.
                        6, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> deeply appreciated your
                        letter<note n="3" xml:id="d276fn3">This is a reference to a letter from
                        President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> which
                            <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> delivered to
                            <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> on his arrival in
                        Bonn; a copy of this letter, which generally explained the purpose of the
                            <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName>–<persName
                            corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Stassen</persName> trip, is in the Conference
                        files, lot 59 D 95, CF 137.</note> and showed us with pride the landscape
                    which you gave him.</p>
                <p>We discussed his desire to come to the United States, and he indicated the first
                    week in April would be best from his point of view, if it were agreeable to you,
                    as he must be back in Germany about mid-April for his party’s national
                    congress.</p>
                <p>If the first week in April is agreeable to you it would mean that <persName
                        corresp="#p_MAYERD1">Mayer</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BIDAULTG1"
                        >Bidault</persName> would come during fourth week in March and then
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> early in April.<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d276fn4">Documentation on <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                            >Adenauer</persName>’s visit to Washington in April 1953 is presented in
                            <ref target="frus1952-54v07p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>
                        </ref>; documentation on <persName corresp="#p_MAYERD1">Mayer</persName>’s
                        visit to Washington in March 1953 is presented in <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v06p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Best regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
